{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-21T14:06:29.006Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"hash table"},{"type":"text","text":" (or hash map) is a data structure that stores "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"key-value pairs"},{"type":"text","text":" and provides "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"O(1) average-time complexity"},{"type":"text","text":" for insertions, deletions, and lookups by using a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"hash function"},{"type":"text","text":" to compute the index where each value is stored. Unlike arrays (index-based) or BSTs (sorted), hash tables use hashing to map arbitrary keys (strings, objects) to array indices, making them ideal for fast lookups, dictionaries, caches, and frequency counting—critical for Gen AI for token vocabulary indexing, caching LLM responses, and feature engineering."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What It Is"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Aspect"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Hash Table"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Array"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"BST"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text